               <msContents>
                  <summary>The Ms. contains the following texts:&#xD; I) Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel, Homiliary
                     for the feasts of St Michael (fol. 1ra-102rb)&#xD; II) Malkǝʾa Mikāʾel “Image
                     of Michael” (fols. 102rb-105vb)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1ra" to="102rb">1ra-102rb</locus>
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT1295Dersan">Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel “Homiliary for the
                        Monthly Feasts of St Michael”</title>

                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        <locus target="#1r">1r, l. 1</locus>በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩ዱ፡ አምላክ፡
                        ንቀድም፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ጺሒፈ፡ ዜና፡ ዕበዩ፡ ወክብሩ፡ ወልዕልሁ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ሊቀ፡ መላእክት፡
                        ይስአል፡ ለነ፡ እምኀበ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላኩ፡ መሐሪ፡ ምሕረት፡ ወሣህል። <foreign xml:lang="en">In
                           the name of the Father, and the Son, and the Holy Spirit, one God. We
                           start with the help of God the High, to write the story of the great, the
                           honoured and the high saint Mikāʾel, the head of the angels…</foreign>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <locus target="#102rb">102rb, l. 24</locus> ተፈጸመ፡ <title type="supplied">ድርሳነ፡ ሚካኤል፡</title> [<locus target="#102va">102va</locus>] በሰላመ፡
                        እግዚአብሔር፡ ወበጸሎተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመነ፡ በዳህና፡ ወበሰላም፡ አሜን።<foreign xml:lang="en"> The Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel is done, by the peace of God and the
                           prayer of Mikāʾel, and glory to God who makes possible to accomplish it
                           well and in peace, amen.</foreign>
                     </explicit>



